<!-- SC_OFF --><div class="md"><p>I have this code added to my init.el which starts mu4e ten seconds after Emacs loads.</p> <pre><code>;; Load mu4e in the background when Emacs starts (run-at-time &quot;10 sec&quot; nil (lambda () (let ((current-prefix-arg &#39;(4))) (call-interactively &#39;mu4e) (message nil)))) </code></pre> <p>The problem is that when it happens my Emacs hangs for a fraction of second. I was wondering if it&#39;s possible to load the mu4e thing in an asynchronous manner.</p> </div><!-- SC_ON --> &#32; submitted by &#32; <a href="https://www.reddit.com/user/zoliky"> /u/zoliky </a> <br/> <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/emacs/comments/werxn7/is_it_possible_to_load_mu4e_asynchronously_in_the/">[link]</a></span> &#32; <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/emacs/comments/werxn7/is_it_possible_to_load_mu4e_asynchronously_in_the/">[comments]</a></span>